<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5747/19–21.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Squiers</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-21"><hi rend="italic">May 21,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root instructs Mr. Squiers to give formal notification to the
                            Panaman Government that Mr. Edward C. Bumpus, of Massachusetts, <pb facs="0774" n="672" xml:id="pg_672"/> and Hon. Edwin Denby, of
                            Michigan, have been appointed as United States commissioners
                            plenipotentiary on the tribunal for the assessment of land under Article
                            VI of the treaty of November 18, 1903, between the United States and
                            Panama.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>